@dpopowich is this still an issue you're facing or are we having more of a theoretical discussion?
`x-nullable` could make this a bit more complicated, _if_ your PATCH endpoint would behave differently for attributes that were passed in with the value `None` vs. them not being passed in at all. From a Swagger spec standpoint both of these cases are equivalent, it means the attribute's value is unknown. `x-nullable` was added to support existing server implementations that don't filter out attributes with `None` values.

I'd much rather tackle this as part of a larger Swagger 3.0 work unless you're running into real issues.

