@alyssa-adams I believe you technically have to have something that other people can view or use in order to get a production key, but I would definitely submit a user note to Riot to ask them. If you layout a somewhat detailed project structure for a PhD project, they may make an exception.

That said, the very first production key I got was for an _extremely_ basic website, so you may be able to spin one up quickly and talk about your PhD project on it, and maybe have some preliminary results with a small dataset. Your funding agency will also love that, so you/your advisor might get major brownie points for the whole Broader Impacts stuff.

So if you can either give them a project outline if you already have one, or if you or a friend can spin up a basic website (maybe even a wordpress site if you are just going to paste in some preliminary results) then I'd guess that you have a good shot at getting a production key.

