@anselor If it proves difficult to solve the performance issues, then maybe we should consider moving the **argcomplete_bridge** functionality to its own module separate from ``cmd2``.  

Personally I like having it inside ``cmd2`` for the "one-stop-shop" aspect of it where ``cmd2`` can help you quickly create features rich interactive command-line interface applications (CLIs) as well as non-interactive command-line utilities (CLUs).  

However, from an architectural perspective the **argcomplete_bridge** code is mostly unrelated to the rest of the ``cmd2`` code base and may be better as a separate module - that way CLUs which want to use it don't need to import anything from ``cmd2`` and won't pay any associated performance/latency penalty.  If you want, it should be very easy to create a new repo underneath the top-level **python-cmd2** organization if you wish.

